[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man 'critical' after being hit by car in Aberdeen

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man in his 30s has been taken to hospital with "life threatening" injuries after being struck by a car in Aberdeen.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident happened on Ellon Road, Bridge of Don, at about 22:30 on Saturday.
The man was taken to Aberdeen Royal Infirmary where his condition has been described as critical.
The road was closed for a number of hours while an investigation was carried out.
